{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2cd76800-5b11-4426-9de4-7064e62d7b14","content":"Here's the mapping:\n\n| VSTest flag | Microsoft.Testing.Platform flag |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `-- --treenode-filter \"/*[Tag=Integration]\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `-- --report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `-- --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `-- --crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `-- --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**New command** (everything after `--` is passed to the test platform):\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/*[Tag=Integration]\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Required NuGet packages** to add to your test project(s):\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"17.*\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n```\n\n**Note:** The `Tag=Integration` filter matches `[TestCategory(\"Integration\")]` in MSTest or `[Trait(\"Category\",\"Integration\")]` in xUnit. Verify the filter shape matches your test framework's mapping — run with `--list-tests` first to inspect the tree.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9301f2b0-5d93-42fd-87ae-a20dbb4ac23e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure - I can answer this directly without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nLet me think about the mapping:\n\n**VSTest command:**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" --logger trx --collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\" --blame-crash --blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents:**\n\n1. `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` → `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` (same, but the filter syntax may differ slightly; actually in MSTest runner, you use `--treenode-filter` or `--filter` depending on the framework. With Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the filter syntax changes. For MSTest, it's `--treenode-filter \"/Integration\"` or you can use `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` if using the compatibility layer. Actually, let me think more carefully.\n\nIn Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the filter syntax differs from VSTest - you'd use `--treenode-filter` with a tree-based path format like `/*[Tag=Integration]`, though if you're using the VSTest bridge compatibility layer, the traditional `--filter` syntax still works. The exact syntax depends on whether you're using the native Microsoft.Testing.Platform approach or maintaining VSTest compatibility.\n\nFor the migration path, the logger, code coverage, crash dump, and hang dump options all have direct equivalents in the new platform - `--report-trx` for TRX output, `--coverage` with format options for code coverage, and `--crashdump` and `--hangdump` with their respective timeout parameters, each requiring their corresponding extension packages. With Microsoft.Testing.Platform, I need to pass the platform-specific options after `--` when using `dotnet test`, though code coverage handling depends on whether I'm using the `--collect` data collector approach or the built-in coverage feature.\n\nI'm realizing I need to account for the required NuGet packages for each feature—`Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` for trx output, `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` for crash dumps, `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` for hang detection, and `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` for coverage—and then construct the command with all those options passed to the platform. The tricky part is getting the filter syntax right for test categories, since MSTest uses `[TestCategory(\"Integration\")]` but I need to map that to the correct MTP filter format.","outputTokens":1695,"requestId":"1BD6:1B074D:20B5CC3:241D012:6A03CEF1"},"id":"a0a43452-687c-470d-a6c6-c9f6cfe3c741","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:08:30.923Z","parentId":"1d121592-1fe6-4c72-8ea4-b489331c8cd6"}
